The point forecasts exhibit a positive trend towards the mean with a slight downward trend observed in the last few forecast horizons. When examining the 3D density intervals, it becomes apparent that the intervals remain relatively stable across all horizons, which can likely be attributed to the regime change effect. Therefore, regime change helps maintain stable forecast uncertainty levels throughout different forecast horizons.
